column5: I'm glad so many enjoyed the photos and my attempt at some Photoshop creativity. Here is the second batch of photos from this past year's fishing on the river. We can all keep dreamng...Alan   For this one, I changed the back lighting and added ink spots                 This last one was made from a series of exposures. It took some time and 'trial & error' to figure out the filmstrip look.

WOW part2 is even better  Love the "I'd rather be golfing" pic.... very cool   but what's that species called?  LOL Thanks for taking the time to post and share with us Alan Again congratulations on some very nice square tails Leechman
Awesome fish and very cool effects once again!
Some real nice fish there.  Thanks for taking the time to put those up.
Some beautiful fish! Would love to get some of those next year! Dave
Great posts! I enjoy catching any species of fish but if I could only go after one it would be SPECKS.... You SIR; have left me with a severe case of envy!!!!!....
some great looking fish and cool photo effects.  haven't seen some beauty specks like that nor fished for them for about 12 years since I lived in The Soo for a while. Those are hog brookies
Another cool little collection of photos Al.
awsome pics......the fact your wearing a glove to tail them is even more impressive
Thats really cool....nice trout too. I'm looking for part 1 now....lol.
